
NORTHERN FOODS TO SELL U.S. UNIT FOR <dlramt>24 MLN DLRS</dlramt>
    LONDON, April 21 - Northern Foods Plc {NFDS.L} said its
{<seller>Northserv Inc</seller>} unit had <status>agreed to sell</status> {<acquired>Flagship Cleaning
Services Inc</acquired>} to {<purchaser>Best Co Inc</purchaser>} of Nevada for <dlramt>24.6 mln dlrs</dlramt>
cash.
    Completion is due on April 30. <acqabr>Flagship</acqabr> is based in
<acqloc>Philadelphia</acqloc> and holds the Sears, Roebuck and Co {S} franchise
for <acqbus>domestic carpet and upholstery cleaning</acqbus> throughout the U.S.
    In the year to end March, 1986, <acqabr>Flagship</acqabr> - then known as
KeyServ - reported pre-tax profits of 2.0 mln dlrs with
end-year assets of 8.4 mln, giving a book profit on disposal of
16.2 mln.
    Northern Foods shares were unchanged at 297p.
